</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="color: white"><sub>بسم الله</sub></span></td>
<td>ENCL:</td>
<td><span style="color: white"><sub>الرحمن الرحيم</sub></span></td>
<td>(3) QĀ'IDAH-SCP SCP-CLASS ITEM DOCUMENTATION</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="color: white"><sub>بسم الله</sub></span></td>
<td><span style="color: white"><sub>الحمد لله</sub></span></td>
<td><span style="color: white"><sub>الرحمن الرحيم</sub></span></td>
<td>(1) ORIA/QĀ'IDAH-SCP CORRESPONDENCE</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>1. We have received your appeal regarding further maintenance of the Bubiyan Outpost. Contrary to rumours, our liaison from the Guardian Council holds no sway over the Central Committee's decisions. ORIA will maintain our study of artefacts from all faiths, including those of the Old Faiths. Our treaty with the Iranian Revolutionary Government has not and will not deteriorate our commitment to study and investigate all artefacts regardless of origin.</p>
<p>2. Nevertheless, it is unfortunate to inform you that ORIA will not reverse its position regarding the closure of the Bubiyan Outpost. As stated above, it is not attributed to the Guardian Council's advocacy for orthodoxy. It is a decision borne from ORIA's stance of pragmatism, as it always has been. Rest assure that this is a calculated move that will ultimately strengthen ORIA's position, as this memorandum shall elaborate.</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>WITH REGARDS TO CLOSURE OF BUBIYAN OUTPOST:</strong></p>
</div>
<p>3. Our study of <a href="/scp-2688">E-NAMMU</a> has been limited since Project 707's initiation, marred by our poor relations with the temple's inhabitants. Several missteps during our initial takeover of the temple have cost us the trust of its inhabitants, who have likely carried that grudge and refuse cooperation despite our offer for entente. Therefore, for decades since, we have effectively maintained an outpost without meaningful exploitation of it. Even now, our knowledge of the temple is limited and superficial. Given this impediment, the Central Committee has vetoed against pouring in additional resources to the Bubiyan Outpost.</p>
<p>4. In addition, ORIA's affiliation with the Islamic Republic of Iran has rendered the Organisation an enemy to both the Iraqi Republic and United States of America. The Iraqi occupation over Kuwait since the previous year has complicated many of our operations there, following our involvement in solidarity with the people of Iran during the Imposed War. As the overseer of the Bubiyan Outpost, you know this better than I &#8212; that this outpost is facing a subtle siege from the Iraqis.</p>
<hr />
<div style="float:right"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/oria-hub/oria.png" width="120px" alt="oria.png" class="image" /></div>
<br />
<span style="font-family: COURIER;"><br /></span>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-family: COURIER;"><span style="font-size:2.5em;"><strong>CONFIDENTIAL</strong></span></span></p>
</div>
<br />
<hr />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<hr />
<div style="float:left">
<table class="wiki-content-table">
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">PROJECT #: PROJECT 707</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">CODENAME: &quot;E-NAMMU&quot;</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">PROJECT HEAD: &quot;IBN SĪNĀ&quot;</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">AUTHOR: &quot;JIBRIL ACTUAL&quot;</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">DESTINATION: BUBIYAN OUTPOST</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">MEMORANDUM 321 &#8212; P2/3</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">14 NOVEMBER 1990</span></td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
<div style="float:right"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/oria-hub/oria.png" width="120px" alt="oria.png" class="image" /></div>
<br />
<span style="font-family: COURIER;"><br /></span>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-family: COURIER;"><span style="font-size:2.5em;"><strong>CONFIDENTIAL</strong></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:1em;">ISLAMIC ARTEFACT RECLAMATION DIRECTORATE</span><br />
<span style="font-size:1em;">SHEMIRAN, TEHRAN PROVINCE</span><br />
<span style="font-size:1em;">ISLAMIC REPUBLIC OF IRAN</span></p>
</div>
<br />
<hr />
<p>5. Regarding the U.S., it is a polity hostile to the current administration at Iran and its government has been convinced by the House of Sabah's machinations to &quot;liberate&quot; Kuwait. Should the U.S. intervene at Kuwait, the Bubiyan Outpost may be targeted by either polities due to a supposed Iranian presence there. Even with hypothetical reinforcements from ORIA Paramilitaries, the risk of collateral damage is estimated to be high. The Organisation certainly does not desire the destruction of E-NAMMU, especially if caused by our involvement in the temple.</p>
<p>6. Furthermore, any destruction of E-NAMMU might be detrimental to the region at large. If you may refer to PROJECT 707 | MEMORANDUM 032, En Babil of the Apkallu has cautioned against any excavation on the temple that could damage the structure.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup> Although the Apkallu's recommendation is to protect E-NAMMU at all costs, it is within the opinion of ORIA Paramilitaries Head &quot;MIKAIL&quot; that ORIA's protection of the temple amidst Saddam Hussein's tactics is infeasible. Should E-NAMMU be damaged, the unknown miasma inside the temple might be unleashed upon the world and it will then be ORIA's failure for the inability to protect the people of Kuwait. The Organisation's very name will be stained.</p>
<p>7. Of course, the Organisation is indeed aware that the abandonment of the Bubiyan Outpost will not necessarily guarantee the preservation of E-NAMMU. As such, ORIA has contacted QĀ'IDAH-SCP to succeed the Organisation as a provisional custodian of the temple. I will immediately highlight that this is <strong>NO</strong> indication or implication of an alliance between ORIA and QĀ'IDAH-SCP, but a mutual agreement intended for mutual benefit. The reasons for this choice are as follows:</p>
<p>8. QĀ'IDAH-SCP's modus operandi forbids the destruction of artefacts in general, hence the preservation of E-NAMMU is likely to be upheld by them. QĀ'IDAH-SCP's lobby in the United States will effectively guarantee U.S. backing for the temple's preservation. Furthermore, Saddam Hussein's regime appears to have an entente with QĀ'IDAH-SCP, which allowed its bases to be maintained on Iraqi territory (of which Kuwait is now part of), e.g. PROJECT 003 (<a href="/dr-clef-s-proposal">&quot;JANNĀT ADNI&quot;</a>). Independent of the conflict's outcome, QĀ'IDAH-SCP seems to be able to guarantee the temple's integrity in the long run.</p>
<p>9. During our correspondence with QĀ'IDAH-SCP, its O5 Council has been pressured by our negotiators and made the wise decision to return several artefacts to ORIA. These artefacts are of great value to ORIA, hence our willingness to engage in this exchange. Details of the three artefacts and specimens are as follow:</p>
<ul>
<li>PROJECT 005 (&quot;KHĀTAM SULAYMĀN&quot;): Thankfully, it appears that QĀ'IDAH-SCP remains ignorant of KHĀTAM SULAYMĀN's true potential and has deemed it an expendable resource. Once reclaimed and verified, it shall be destroyed pursuant to the ORIA/Afsenah Pact. The bondage of <em>djinns</em> is an outdated notion in the modern era of human-<em>djinn</em> relations, and KHĀTAM SULAYMĀN's destruction will be ORIA's declaration of sincerity.</li>
<li>PROJECT 112 (<a href="/scp-112-arc">&quot;CHASTE IDOL&quot;</a>): Following Mohammadien's Idol Hypothesis, the CHASTE IDOL will be of significance to our efforts to investigate the <em>true</em> history of the Arabian Peninsula. Although the maintenance of the CHASTE IDOL does require <em>castrati</em> attendants, we can rally the Galli to provide attendants to the CHASTE IDOL.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<div style="float:right"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/oria-hub/oria.png" width="120px" alt="oria.png" class="image" /></div>
<br />
<span style="font-family: COURIER;"><br /></span>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-family: COURIER;"><span style="font-size:2.5em;"><strong>CONFIDENTIAL</strong></span></span></p>
</div>
<br />
<hr />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<hr />
<div style="float:left">
<table class="wiki-content-table">
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">PROJECT #: PROJECT 707</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
