</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">PROJECT HEAD: &quot;IBN SĪNĀ&quot;</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">AUTHOR: &quot;JIBRIL ACTUAL&quot;</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">DESTINATION: BUBIYAN OUTPOST</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">MEMORANDUM 321 &#8212; P3/3</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span style="font-size:0.75em;">14 NOVEMBER 1990</span></td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
<div style="float:right"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/oria-hub/oria.png" width="120px" alt="oria.png" class="image" /></div>
<br />
<span style="font-family: COURIER;"><br /></span>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-family: COURIER;"><span style="font-size:2.5em;"><strong>CONFIDENTIAL</strong></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:1em;">ISLAMIC ARTEFACT RECLAMATION DIRECTORATE</span><br />
<span style="font-size:1em;">SHEMIRAN, TEHRAN PROVINCE</span><br />
<span style="font-size:1em;">ISLAMIC REPUBLIC OF IRAN</span></p>
</div>
<br />
<hr />
<ul>
<li>PROJECT 232 (<a href="/scp-232-arc">&quot;EREŠ.KI.GAL&quot;</a>): Its reclamation will surely placate the much-disgruntled Apkallu, whom you have defended on many occasions. While QĀ'IDAH-SCP's document suggest that it has faced difficulty handling EREŠ.KI.GAL, the Apkallu's knowledge of appropriate rites will render it manageable for long-term study.</li>
</ul>
<p>10. Should the worst occur and E-NAMMU is breached under QĀ'IDAH-SCP's custodianship (for whatever reason), blame will be placed on QĀ'IDAH-SCP and they will be further discredited among Dar al-Islam. Polities sympathetic of QĀ'IDAH-SCP will be more compelled to side with the Organisation as a stronger alternative. That said, this is only a worst-case scenario. Disregarding the shortcomings in securing a dhimmity over E-NAMMU, the Organisation's proper application of Pagan wisdom definitely kept the miasma inside dormant (which shall be our official stance on the matter). If it is made active by QĀ'IDAH-SCP's hand, it is certainly attributed to their flawed methods to cast aside Pagan wisdom (and that would be suitable counter-evidence to assertions that Pagan wisdom is <em>haram</em> to ORIA.)</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>WITH REGARDS TO EXCHANGE OF ARTEFACTS:</strong></p>
</div>
<p>11. To facilitate the exchange of artefacts without damaging ORIA's image and mission statement, the Bubiyan Outpost will be &quot;invaded&quot; by a task force from QĀ'IDAH-SCP. Officially, they are agents of QĀ'IDAH-SCP tasked to claim E-NAMMU amidst the chaos of war. Date of exchange is to be confirmed on a later date, however it is agreed upon to occur during the eventual U.S. intervention.</p>
<p>12. Prior to the date of exchange, a majority of operatives in Bubiyan Outpost will be reassigned to other locations in ORIA's sphere of influence. A skeleton crew will maintain daily operations in the outpost until the date of exchange. During the &quot;invasion&quot;, you are allowed to retaliate with valour. However, you must surrender to QĀ'IDAH-SCP with minimal loss of lives (on both sides). As per our correspondences with QĀ'IDAH-SCP, the skeleton crew will be held temporarily until a prisoner exchange that will occur one week after the artefacts exchange.</p>
<p>13. With regards to the three artefacts currently held by QĀ'IDAH-SCP, safe-houses that are currently carrying them will be made available for our operatives to reclaim without significant fatalities. A number of prisoners may also be taken from QĀ'IDAH-SCP in the course of these operations, who will then be involved in the aforementioned prisoner exchange.</p>
<p>14. Despite the apparent sign of &quot;joint effort&quot;, the Organisation's enmity towards QĀ'IDAH-SCP still stands. This decision is one of mutual benefit, more so for ORIA in fact. We hope you may agree to assist in securing the Bubiyan Outpost for QĀ'IDAH-SCP. If you are unwilling to be associated with this dishonour, the Organisation permits you to be transferred prior to the date of exchange and allow another to take the position of IBN SĪNĀ.</p>
<p>15. This memorandum drafted and transmitted 14 November 1990.</p>
<p>&#8212; &quot;JIBRIL ACTUAL&quot;</p>
<hr />
